Issues.Body:
### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

We have the following component in our component library: 

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'button[edsUserMenuTrigger]',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [SlicePipe, NgIf, NgClass, MatIconModule, LetDirective],
  templateUrl: './user-menu-trigger.component.html',
  hostDirectives: [
    {
      directive: CdkMenuTrigger,
      inputs: ['cdkMenuTriggerFor:forMenu'],
    },
  ],
})
```

This is how we use it in our application:

```html
<button edsUserMenuTrigger [forMenu]="menu"></button>
<ng-template #menu>
  ...
</ng-template>
```

In the application it works totally fine.

The unit tests for the component that uses this look like this: 

```typescript
describe('UserMenuComponent', () => {
  let spectator: Spectator<UserMenuComponent>;
  let component: UserMenuComponent;

  const createComponent = createComponentFactory({
    imports: [],
    component: UserMenuComponent,
  });
  beforeEach(() => {
    spectator = createComponent();
    component = spectator.component;
  });
  it('should be created', () => {
    expect(component).toBeTruthy();
  });
});
```

Starting the unit tests always throws the following error immediately:

<img width="827" alt="Bildschirmfoto 2023-07-20 um 08 57 55" src="https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/1453455/190c1edc-86e1-46f1-93dd-64406472834a">


Any idea what could be the cause or how to fix this?

